House Bill 700
By: Representatives Adesanya of the 43rd, Beckles of the 96th, and Draper of the 90th
A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Code Section 10-1-393.3 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
2 prohibited use of purchaser's credit card information by merchant, so as to limit the amount
3 of surcharges charged by merchants for purchasers using credit cards; to provide for related
4 matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
5 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
6 SECTION 1.
7 Code Section 10-1-393.3 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to prohibited
8 use of purchaser's credit card information by merchant, is amended by adding a new
9 subsection to read as follows:
10 "(d.1) A merchant shall be prohibited from requiring a purchaser using a credit card for
11 any transaction to pay a surcharge in an amount that exceeds the actual cost to the merchant
12 to process the transaction."
13 SECTION 2.
14 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
